gw.api.domain

Interface CoverableAdapterWithReferenceDateInternalOverride

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CoverableAbstractDomainMethods, CoverableAdapter

    public interface CoverableAdapterWithReferenceDateInternalOverride
extends CoverableAdapter
    This interface provides a way for Coverable entities that have a persistent field named "ReferenceDateInternal" to override the default behavior of the getter and setter for that field.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getReferenceDateInternal

        java.util.Date getReferenceDateInternal()
        Description copied from interface: CoverableAdapter
        Returns the internal reference date persisted on this Coverable. This date should be null for all newly created Coverables in an unbound job and for all Coverables in a Rewrite or Renewal. Conversely, the date should be non-null for all Coverables in a bound PolicyPeriod and for pre-existing Coverables in an unbound midterm change.
        Specified by:
        getReferenceDateInternal in interface CoverableAdapter
        Returns:
        the reference date persisted with the delegating entity

      • setReferenceDateInternal

        void setReferenceDateInternal(java.util.Date date)
        Description copied from interface: CoverableAdapter
        Sets the internal reference date of this Coverable. This is called when binding a PolicyPeriod if the Coverable's internal reference date is not already set, and when creating a new policy term to clear the persisted date.
        Specified by:
        setReferenceDateInternal in interface CoverableAdapter
        Parameters:
        date - the reference date to be persisted with the delegating entity
